- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the creation of a dataset for detecting deepfakes using facial modification algorithms. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the dataset consists of videos with arbitrary backgrounds, bringing visual variability. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper discusses the need for detecting deepfakes, which can be used for malicious purposes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of specific metrics to evaluate the performance of deepfake detection models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of deepfake detection models and the need for developing better algorithms to detect deepfakes.
